data.description: NEUSE RIVER HIGH ELEVATION WATERFRONT 1950'S RAMBLER READY FOR A MAKEOVER.....If you have been searching for a beautiful spot overlooking the Neuse River to create your dream home, this 1950's Rambler on 3 plus acres perched high above the Neuse River is it!  What an opportunity here to bring this 'grande dame' back to her splendor.  Over 3,000 square feet, 3 bedroom, 2 bath, plus an office has a huge living room with brick wood burning fireplace that combines with open concept formal dining area overlooking the Neuse.  Some hardwood flooring just revealed, a beautiful layout, an amazing great room with 9' ceilings and gas log brick fireplace, the perfect spot for gatherings.  A window filled sun room leads to screened porch overlooking river.  The original eat in kitchen leads to an adjacent butler's pantry/laundry room with great storage that leads down to great room. The primary suite, tucked at end of hall, is tremendous with full bath and walk in closet.  There are two good size bedrooms off hall, a full bath with tile floor and tiled stall shower and separate tub.  There is even an office or den with large window overlooking yard and river.  Ample closets throughout.  A detached 2 car garage off great room through covered breezeway includes a workspace.  Road front of property has split rail fencing and outbuilding that once housed a horse.  Mature trees and landscape flank a large grassed area.Improvements per Estate, roof April 2019, one new Trane A/C unit Feb 2023, new internal drip pan on air handler Aug 2023. Home selling with no repairs made by Estate.  Marketed below appraised value.
